# DialogueBridge smoke test.
#
# This file demonstrates a variety of useful Dialogue Manager features:
# - titles
# - choices
# - typing speed and pauses
# - animated text with BBCode-like effects
# - bridge helper calls
# - session values through the bridge
# - context node method calls
# - audio through AudioManager-backed context methods
# - tags such as #voice
# - imported snippets
# - weighted random groups
# - conditional choices

import "res://data/dialogues/tests/dialogue_bridge_smoke_snippets.dialogue" as snippets

~ start
do DialogueBridge.call_context_node_method("dialogue_smoke", "add_visit")
Guide: Welcome to the DialogueBridge smoke test.
Guide: The visit count is now {{DialogueBridge.session_get_data("dialogue/visit_count", 0)}}.
Guide: Pick a chapter to inspect one feature at a time.
- Typing, pauses and animated text => typing_demo
- Bridge helpers and session values => bridge_demo
- Context node methods => context_demo
- Audio, tags and voice => audio_demo
- Import and jump-and-return => import_demo
- Weighted random lines => random_demo
- Conditional choice demo [if DialogueBridge.session_get_flag("dialogue/demo_key", false)] => unlocked_demo
- End the conversation => END


~ alt_start
Guide: This alternative start jumps directly to a smaller demo branch.
Guide: It is useful to test that DialogueBridge.start_dialogue(resource, start_title) works as expected.
- Go to the context demo => context_demo
- Go to the audio demo => audio_demo
- Back to the main menu => start


~ typing_demo
Guide: [speed=0.35]This line types slowly, then it pauses.[wait=0.25] Then it continues.
Guide: Rich text works too: [wave amp=25 freq=5]wave[/wave], [shake rate=20 level=8]shake[/shake], and [rainbow freq=0.3 sat=0.8 val=0.9]rainbow[/rainbow].
do DialogueBridge.call_context_node_method("dialogue_smoke", "play_demo_ui")
Guide: The previous line also triggered a UI sound through the registered context.
Guide: This line advances automatically after a short delay.[next=0.9]
=> start


~ bridge_demo
do DialogueBridge.session_set_flag("dialogue/demo_key", true)
do DialogueBridge.session_set_data("dialogue/demo_note", "The bridge wrote this value from the dialogue file.")
do DialogueBridge.session_set_data("dialogue/demo_branch", "bridge_demo")
do DialogueBridge.call_context_node_method("dialogue_smoke", "mark_tutorial_seen")
do DialogueBridge.call_context_node_method("dialogue_smoke", "rename_player", ["Guilhem"])
do DialogueBridge.call_context_node_method("dialogue_smoke", "increment_demo_counter")
Guide: Dialogue can write values through the bridge.
Guide: dialogue/demo_key is now {{DialogueBridge.session_get_flag("dialogue/demo_key", false)}}.
Guide: dialogue/demo_note is now "{{DialogueBridge.session_get_data("dialogue/demo_note", "<missing>")}}".
Guide: dialogue/player_name is now {{DialogueBridge.session_get_data("dialogue/player_name", "Hero")}}.
Guide: The newly unlocked conditional choice is now available in the start menu.
=> start


~ context_demo
do DialogueBridge.call_context_node_method("dialogue_smoke", "mark_context_pinged")
do DialogueBridge.call_context_node_method("dialogue_smoke", "set_panel_message_intro")
Guide: Dialogue can call methods on a registered scene object through DialogueBridge.
Guide: The current context mood is {{DialogueBridge.get_context_value("dialogue_smoke", "demo_mood", "unknown")}}.
- Cycle the preview color
	do DialogueBridge.call_context_node_method("dialogue_smoke", "cycle_demo_box_color")
	do DialogueBridge.call_context_node_method("dialogue_smoke", "remember_choice", ["cycle_color"])
	Guide: The preview box color just changed.
	=> context_demo
- Set the mood to happy
	do DialogueBridge.call_context_node_method("dialogue_smoke", "set_mood_happy")
	do DialogueBridge.call_context_node_method("dialogue_smoke", "remember_choice", ["happy"])
	Guide: The context mood is now {{DialogueBridge.get_context_value("dialogue_smoke", "demo_mood", "unknown")}}.
	=> context_demo
- Set the mood to surprised
	do DialogueBridge.call_context_node_method("dialogue_smoke", "set_mood_surprised")
	do DialogueBridge.call_context_node_method("dialogue_smoke", "remember_choice", ["surprised"])
	Guide: The context mood is now {{DialogueBridge.get_context_value("dialogue_smoke", "demo_mood", "unknown")}}.
	=> context_demo
- Back to the main menu
	=> start


~ audio_demo
Guide: Audio can be triggered by code called from the dialogue.
- Play music
	do DialogueBridge.call_context_node_method("dialogue_smoke", "play_demo_music")
	Guide: Demo music was started through the context method.
	=> audio_demo
- Play alternate music
	do DialogueBridge.call_context_node_method("dialogue_smoke", "play_alt_demo_music")
	Guide: Alternate music was started through the context method.
	=> audio_demo
- Play a gameplay sound effect
	do DialogueBridge.call_context_node_method("dialogue_smoke", "play_demo_sfx")
	Guide: A sound effect just played.
	=> audio_demo
- Play another sound effect
	do DialogueBridge.call_context_node_method("dialogue_smoke", "play_alt_demo_sfx")
	Guide: A second sound effect just played.
	=> audio_demo
- Play a UI click
	do DialogueBridge.call_context_node_method("dialogue_smoke", "play_demo_ui")
	Guide: A UI sound just played.
	=> audio_demo
- Play a bubble UI sound
	do DialogueBridge.call_context_node_method("dialogue_smoke", "play_demo_bubble")
	Guide: A bubble UI sound just played.
	=> audio_demo
- Stop all audio
	do DialogueBridge.call_context_node_method("dialogue_smoke", "stop_demo_audio")
	Guide: All audio was stopped.
	=> audio_demo
- Show a line with a voice tag
	Guide [#voice=res://audio/ui/CGM3_Dialogue_Text_01_1.wav]: This line uses the default example balloon's voice tag support.
	=> audio_demo
- Back to the main menu
	=> start


~ import_demo
Guide: The next command jumps to an imported title and then comes back here.
=>< snippets/imported_lesson
Guide: We returned from the imported snippet.
Guide: dialogue/import_seen is now {{DialogueBridge.session_get_flag("dialogue/import_seen", false)}}.
=> start


~ random_demo
Guide: The three lines below belong to one weighted random group.
% Guide: This is the default random line.
%2 Guide: This line is twice as likely to appear.
%0.25 Guide: This rare line only appears sometimes.
Guide: After the random group, the dialogue continues normally.
=> start


~ unlocked_demo
Guide: This title only becomes available after the bridge demo sets dialogue/demo_key to true.
Guide: dialogue/demo_branch currently says {{DialogueBridge.session_get_data("dialogue/demo_branch", "<missing>")}}.
Guide: dialogue/last_choice currently says {{DialogueBridge.session_get_data("dialogue/last_choice", "<missing>")}}.
=> start